description: PHILADELPHIA (AP) — Matt Olson doubled three times, including a bases-loaded drive in a seven-run eighth inning that rallied the NL East champion Atlanta Braves past the Philadelphia Phillies 9-3 in Friday’s season opener.
title: Braves rally in the seventh inning to defeat the Mets

description: WASHINGTON (AP) — Cade Cunningham scored 33 points, Jalen Duren had 20 points and 18 rebounds and Detroit snapped an eight-game losing streak with a victory over Washington on Friday night.
title: Pistons beat the Wizards 96-87, snapping an 8-game skid

description: Dennis Schroder and Mikal Bridges each made seven 3-pointers, and the Brooklyn Nets tied an NBA record by making 18 3s in the second half of their 125-108 victory over the Chicago Bulls on Friday night.
title: Nets tie NBA record with 18 3-pointers in a half, beat Bulls 125-108

description: Ke’Bryan Hayes had a single and an RBI double, and the Pittsburgh Pirates used another solid pitching outing to beat the Marlins 7-2 on Friday night. Michael A.
title: Hayes hits single and RBI double, Pirates pitching remains sharp in 7-2 win over Marlins

description: DALLAS (AP) — DJ Horne scored 19 points and North Carolina State kept its magical NCAA Tournament run alive, beating Marquette 67-58 on Friday night to reach the Elite Eight for the first time since 1986.
title: N.C. State beats Marquette 67-58 to keep magical March Madness run alive

description: Jackson Holliday homered leading off the first inning and had three hits and four RBIs, starting the Triple-A season by helping Baltimore’s Norfolk Tides beat Tampa Bay’s Durham Bulls 12-8 on Friday night in the International League.
title: Top Orioles prospect Jackson Holliday homers, has 3 hits, 4 RBIs in Triple-A opener

description: ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) — Oregon State’s bigs played huge and the Beavers held Notre Dame star Hannah Hidalgo in check on Friday to advance to the program’s first regional final in six years.
title: Oregon State beats Notre Dame 70-65 in Sweet 16

description: Presumptive Republican presidential nominee Donald Trump is drawing criticism for posting a video on social media Friday that contains the image of a hog-tied President Joe Biden painted on the tailgate of a passing truck.
title: Trump posts video with an image of a hog-tied Biden, drawing a rebuke from Democrat's campaign

description: Ontario’s Niagara Region has declared a state of emergency as it prepares to welcome up to a million visitors for the solar eclipse in early April.
title: Canada's Niagara region declares a state of emergency to prepare for an influx of eclipse viewers

description: Hannah Green birdied the final six holes for a career-low 11-under 61 on Friday in the LPGA Tour Ford Championship, giving her a one-shot lead going into the weekend.
title: Hannah Green shoots 11-under 61 to take 1-shot lead at LPGA Ford Championship

description: High winds and turbulence have forced a United Airlines flight from Israel to be diverted from its destination of Newark Airport in New Jersey to Stewart International Airport in New Windsor, New York.
title: High winds and turbulence force flight from Israel to New Jersey to be diverted to New York state

description: World Rugby Player of the Year Ardie Savea has tentatively endorsed a suggested policy change which would allow players based outside New Zealand to be considered for All Blacks selection.
title: Ardie Savea tentatively backs All Blacks selection for offshore players

description: Tage Thompson’s scored four times, including the go-ahead goal with 4:34 remaining, and the Buffalo Sabres beat the Devils 5-2 to put a dent in New Jersey’s late-season playoff push.
title: Tage Thompson's 4-goal night rallies Buffalo Sabres to 5-2 win over the New Jersey Devils

description: Aziaha James had 29 points and third-seeded North Carolina State earned its third trip to the women's Elite Eight with a 77-67 victory over second-seeded Stanford.
title: Aziaha James scores 29 to lead N.C. State into the women's Elite Eight with 77-67 win over Stanford

description: Purdue big man Zach Edey withstood all the abuse Gonzaga could lay on him, finishing with 27 points and 14 rebounds to lift the Boilermakers to an 80-68 victory and move them one win from the Final Four.
title: Sweet 16 nets another big win for Purdue and big man Zach Edey, 80-68 over Gonzaga

description: The Boston Red Sox removed third baseman Rafael Devers from the starting lineup before Friday night’s game against the Seattle Mariners because of left shoulder soreness.
title: Rafael Devers scratched from Red Sox lineup before game vs. Mariners because of shoulder soreness

description: DJ Horne scored 19 points and North Carolina State kept its magical NCAA Tournament run alive, beating Marquette 67-58 to reach the Elite Eight for the first time since 1986.
title: N.C. State keeps magical March Madness run alive with 67-58 win over Marquette

description: Aaron Civale allowed one run over six innings and Brandon Lowe hit his fourth career grand slam to lead the Tampa Bay Rays to a 8-2 victory over the Toronto Blue Jays.
title: Civale sparkles, Lowe hits 4th career grand slam to propel Rays over Blue Jays 8-2

description: Pascal Siakam had 22 points and 11 rebounds, while Tyrese Haliburton finished with 21 points and eight assists to lead the Indiana Pacers past the Los Angeles Lakers 109-90 in a pivotal game for both teams’ playoff aspirations.
title: Pascal Siakam, Tyrese Haliburton combine for 43 points to lead Pacers past Lakers 109-90

description: Stephen Curry scored 23 points with four 3-pointers in his annual Charlotte homecoming game and the Golden State Warriors defeated the Hornets 115-97 for their third straight win.
title: Stephen Curry returns home, scores 23 points to lead Warriors past Hornets 115-97

description: Cade Cunningham scored 33 points, Jalen Duren had 20 points and 18 rebounds and the Detroit Pistons snapped an eight-game losing streak with a 96-87 victory over the Washington Wizards on Friday night.
title: Pistons snap 8-game skid, beating the Wizards 96-87 in a matchup of the NBA's bottom 2 teams

description: Grant Nelson made himself a part of Alabama basketball history with his dominant performance against North Carolina.
title: Grant Nelson has confidence back as Alabama takes on Clemson in West Region final

description: SPARKS, Nev. (AP) — Police surrounded a house in a residential Sparks neighborhood Friday where they said a suspect in an officer-involved shooting was barricaded inside shortly after two law enforcement officers were shot and hospitalized with unspecified injuries.
title: 2 police officers shot in Nevada city. SWAT team surrounds home where suspect reportedly holed up

description: Mackenzie Holmes’ stellar career at Indiana is over after a loss to top-seeded South Carolina in the Sweet 16.
title: Mackenzie Holmes ends stellar career at Indiana with loss in the Sweet 16 to South Carolina

description: Sacramento Kings guard Kevin Huerter will miss the rest of the season with plans to undergo left shoulder surgery to repair a torn labrum, coach Mike Brown confirmed.
title: Sacramento Kings' Kevin Huerter to undergo season-ending shoulder surgery

description: Alabama and Clemson facing off on a Saturday sounds like it ought to be happening on a football field.
title: Alabama and Clemson are known for their football prowess. They face off for a spot in the Final Four

description: The Denver Nuggets are missing Jamal Murray for their showdown against the Minnesota Timberwolves on Friday night in Denver.
title: Denver Nuggets point guard Jamal Murray out against Timberwolves, missing 4th straight game

description: Lionel Messi’s hamstring injury will keep him sidelined for Inter Miami’s home game against New York City FC on Saturday, but he could return for the CONCACAF Champions Cup quarterfinal first leg against Mexico's Monterrey on April 3.
title: Lionel Messi will miss Miami's game against NYCFC, could return for Champions Cup quarterfinal

description: Brazilian Supreme Court Justice Alexandre de Moraes has denied a request by former president Jair Bolsonaro that his passport be returned to him so that he can travel to Israel.
title: Bolsonaro's request for passport return to travel to Israel denied by Brazil's top court
